e=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zrh1665702776725.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zrh1665702776725.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zrh1665702776725.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zrh1665702776725\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      DB2 Service Stored Procedures\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">DB2 service stored procedures can be invoked by creating a Uniface signature and using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> ProcScript command.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__topic_d49490e1_d49491e1_d49492e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49493e1_d49494e1_d49495e1\">To create and activate a stored procedure in a DB2 database:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__li_d24047e1_d24048e1_d24049e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49496e1_d49497e1_d49498e1\">Create the procedure in DB2.\n For rules on defining and invoking a stored procedure within DB2, refer to the DB2 <cite class=\"cite\">Application Programming Manual</cite>\n</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__li_d24050e1_d24051e1_d24052e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49499e1_d49500e1_d49501e1\">In Uniface, create a Stored Procedure signature to represent the stored procedure.\n Uniface supports Unicode in stored procedure parameters. Parameters with type GRAPHIC can be used to pass UTF16 data to and from a stored procedure. Parameters with type CHAR can be used to pass UTF8 data to and from a stored procedure as long as<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span>is <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF8</code>Ensure that the signature of the procedure uses the corresponding Uniface data type. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"awm1665702727177.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/awm1665702727177.html\" title=\"Uniface data types and packing codes are mapped to DB2 storage formats.\">DB2 Data Packing</a>\n</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__li_d24053e1_d24054e1_d24055e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49502e1_d49503e1_d49504e1\">Make the stored procedure signature available to the Uniface Server or application that is to run the stored procedure.\n Depending on the location of the compiled signature, you can copy it to the target location or UAR and move it to the target location via the deployment utility, FTP, or some other means.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__li_d24056e1_d24057e1_d24058e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49505e1_d49506e1_d49507e1\">Add the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$SSP</code> path to your assignment file:\n The <var class=\"keyword varname\">Server</var>parameter is optional.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$DB2 DB2:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Server</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2User</var>|<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var> \n$SSP $DB2</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__li_d24059e1_d24060e1_d24061e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49508e1_d49509e1_d49510e1\">Invoke the stored procedure via the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> ProcScript statement.\n For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">activate \"MYSCHEMA\".mystoredproc(\"A\", $2)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49511e1_d49512e1_d49513e1\">This runs the stored procedure name ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">mystoredproc</code>’, residing in schema ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">MYSCHEMA</code>’ and defined by signature ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">MYSCHEMA</code>’, passing one input parameter ‘<code class=\"ph codeph\">A</code>’ and one output parameter <code class=\"ph codeph\">$2</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zrh1665702776725__p_d49514e1_d49515e1_d49516e1\">It is also possible to invoke stored procedures using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">call</code>SQL instruction. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gsb1665702776794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gsb1665702776794.html\" title=\"DB2 does not support dynamic use of the CALL SQL statement. However, the connector allows the use of CALL in the Uniface ProcScript language and in the SQL workbench. The sql ProcScript statement is used to pass a CALL statement and parameters.\">Calling Stored Procedures from SQL</a>\n</p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534574\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534574\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DB2 Service Stored Procedures Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DB2 Service Stored Procedures DB2 service stored procedures can be invoked by creating a Uniface signature and using the activate ProcScript command. To create and activate a stored procedure in a DB2 database: Create the procedure in DB2. For rules on defining and invoking a stored procedure within DB2, refer to the DB2 Application Programming Manual In Uniface, create a Stored Procedure signature to represent the stored procedure. Uniface supports Unicode in stored procedure parameters. Parameters with type GRAPHIC can be used to pass UTF16 data to and from a stored procedure. Parameters with type CHAR can be used to pass UTF8 data to and from a stored procedure as long as $DEF_CHARSET is UTF8 Ensure that the signature of the procedure uses the corresponding Uniface data type. For more information, see DB2 Data Packing Make the stored procedure signature available to the Uniface Server or application that is to run the stored procedure. Depending on the location of the compiled signature, you can copy it to the target location or UAR and move it to the target location via the deployment utility, FTP, or some other means. Add the $SSP path to your assignment file: The Server parameter is optional. $DB2 DB2: Server : DatabaseName | DB2User | DB2Password $SSP $DB2 Copy Invoke the stored procedure via the activate ProcScript statement. For example: activate \"MYSCHEMA\".mystoredproc(\"A\", $2) Copy This runs the stored procedure name ‘ mystoredproc ’, residing in schema ‘ MYSCHEMA ’ and defined by signature ‘ MYSCHEMA ’, passing one input parameter ‘ A ’ and one output parameter $2 It is also possible to invoke stored procedures using the call SQL instruction. For more information, see Calling Stored Procedures from SQL Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}